19 hours. Multiple locations. A race against time, weather, and every unpredictable twist the day could throw at us. But when you’re building something this raw, this real—you surrender to the chaos. What kept us going wasn’t just the clock. It was the quiet knowing that we were creating something that would linger.
To work with a team so seasoned, so soulfully in sync, and to be guiding a legend @aroyfloyd whose words carry generations of emotion— Nei Tumi Ager Moto became more than a project.
It became a feeling. A storm we lived through together.
And in the end, we made not just a music video —but a memory that breathes.
